Multi-Source BFS

Normal BFS:

q.offer(startNode);

One starting point.

Rotting Oranges:

Every rotten orange starts spreading simultaneously.

So:

for(all cells) {

    if(grid[r][c] == 2) {

        q.offer(new Pair(r,c));
    }
}

We push all rotten oranges into the queue before BFS starts.

Whenever you hear:

Multiple starting points
Spread simultaneously
Nearest source

Think:

Multi-Source BFS

